       <div class="wrap">
        <div class="block text-block">
         <h3 class="block-header">
          Welcome to
          <span>
           SHOP
          </span>
         </h3>
         <div class="inner">
          <p>
           SHOP is UCSC's Student Health Outreach and Promotion Program and a destination for information. SHOP is where students can go to learn about health and wellness in a safe, non-judgmental environment.
          </p>
          <p>
           SHOP offers information, education, resources and support on issues such as Alcohol and other Drug Use, Sexually Transmitted Infections and Sexual Health, and College Life balance. All UCSC students are welcome and encouraged to drop in and speak with SHOP's trained staff.
          </p>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
       <div class="wrap">
        <div class="block text-block">
         <h3 class="block-header">
          SHOP
          <span>
           NEWS
          </span>
         </h3>
         <div class="inner">
          <p>
           <a href="alcohol-other-drugs/aa.html" title="Cove Recovery Groups">
            <strong>
             Winter schedule
            </strong>
            for The COVE's  drug and alcohol recovery groups!
           </a>
           Click the flyers below to expand.
          </p>
          <p>
           <a href="alcohol-other-drugs/images/the-cove-official-flyer-40per.jpg" title="The Cove is a substance-free, safe space that offers UCSC students support. We welcome students recovering from alcohol and/or other drugs, loved ones of those with addictions, allies, and anyone else who supports recovery and wants a healthy, substance-free safe environment. We are open Monday-Friday 10 AM to 5 PM.">
            <img alt="Thumbnail for The Cove official flyer" class="" height="80" src="alcohol-other-drugs/images/the-cove-official-flyer_80h1.jpg" width="57"/>
           </a>
           <a href="alcohol-other-drugs/winter-2019-recovery-meetings-final_600w_40per.jpg">
            <img alt="Thumbnail for the Cove's Winter 2019 meetings" class="" height="80" src="alcohol-other-drugs/images/winter-2019-recovery-meetings-80h.jpg" width="57"/>
           </a>
           <a href="alcohol-other-drugs/clarareduceduse2official_40per.jpg">
            <img alt="Thumbnail for Reduced Marijuana Use group" class="" height="80" src="alcohol-other-drugs/clarareduceduse2official_80h.jpg" width="61"/>
           </a>
           <a href="alcohol-other-drugs/t.a.s.c._poster-40per.jpg">
            <img alt="Thumbnail for TASC Trans and Substances Community flyer" class="" height="80" src="alcohol-other-drugs/t.a.s.c._poster_80h.jpg" width="63"/>
           </a>
          </p>
          <p>
           <strong>
            The COVE has a podcast
           </strong>
           . Listen to recovery interviews from UCSC Students and discussions on self care, recovery and harm reduction techniques.
           <a href="https://soundcloud.com/thecovecast">
            Listen to the podcast here.
           </a>
          </p>
          <p>
           <a href="sexual-health/bcp.html">
            <strong>
             Birth Control Patrol
            </strong>
            is here! Click for more information.
           </a>
          </p>
          <p>
           <strong>
            Welltrack self-help tools
           </strong>
           : Visit the CAPS website to learn more about the
           <a href="http://caps.ucsc.edu/resources/welltrack.html">
            Welltrack service.
           </a>
          </p>
          <p>
           <a href="http://caps.ucsc.edu/resources/welltrack.html">
            <img alt="Welltrack Billboard" height="96" src="images/welltrack-billboard.png" width="300"/>
           </a>
          </p>
